 Reported by nicolas.raoul on 2011-12-20 09:13:48

		Originally reported on Google Code with ID 1061 What steps will reproduce the problem?
1. Select "type answers" in preferences.
2. Start review with a deck where cardmodel does not specify an answer.


What is the expected output? What do you see instead?
You are prompted for an answer. If I wanted to be prompted for
an answer in this deck, I would have specified it in the card model.

I know that this behavior is intended, but it's anoying. I review three decks every
day and I have to switch this preference if I change the deck. I have also a deck where
for some cards I have an answer specified and for other cards not.

This patch fixes the error. (The info text in preferences needs to be changed too)

diff --git a/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java b/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java
index c0d241d..29e18e1 100644
--- a/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java
+++ b/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java
@@ -1078,8 +1078,8 @@
        String typeAnswer = myCardModel.getTypeAnswer();
         // Check if we have a valid field to use as the answer to type.
        if (null == typeAnswer || 0 == typeAnswer.trim().length()) {
-       // no field specified, compare with whole answer
-           returnArray[0] = mAnswer;
+       // no field specified, return null
+           returnArray[0] = null;
            returnArray[1] = "";
                 return returnArray;
        }
 Reported by thesing.thomas on 2012-03-14 19:57:54

		Originally reported on Google Code with ID 1119 I have a deck with the following fields:

1. French
2. German
3. Audio

Then I created three templates like this:

1.
{{French}}
--
{{German}}
{{Audio}}

2.
{{German}}
--
{{French}}
{{Audio}}

3.
{{Audio}}
--
{{French}}
{{German}}


The first two cards will always be created, because you usually always type in the
German and French fields. But the Audio field is sometimes empty.
Anki Desktop only creates a card if the question field is not empty. So in this case,
if Audio is empty, only two cards are created.

It would be really nice if Ankidroid could do this, too. You can deselect the third
templates, but you forget this sometimes or rather you forget to activate it again
(and then you wonder why you don't have the third card anymore). 

I guess it would be quite easy: Just check if the front page of a card/template is
empty, and if yes, don't create that particular card. 
 Reported by gerritsangel on 2012-04-26 12:43:07

Originally reported on Google Code with ID 1242 What version of AnkiDroid are you using? AnkiDroid v2.0beta6
On what version of Android? 2.2 and 4.1 (emulator)
Any elements that have been given a font-size style do not scale if using "em" as the unit. E.g,. .card { font-size: 2em; }
On the desktop client, the fonts in the card are scaled accordingly. On AnkiDroid, they do not scale. Changing the "Relative font size" has no effect on the text size, whether it's 10% or 150%.
Using pixels instead does indeed scale the text. I.e., the following does get scaled: .card { font-size: 25px; }
The issue is present in cards where the usage of px and em is intermixed among different elements, where those that use px are scaled, and those that use em are not. Reported by Houssam.Salem.Au on 2012-07-21 05:43:18

